  </p>

  <p>
    Ruby fuels one of the most advanced web application frameworks available,
    Rails &#8211; also know as Ruby on Rails.
    Rails is a full-stack framework capable of creating web applications
    that gather information from a database
    and then render results for users to view and interact with.
    Rails emphasizes the use of well-known software engineering patterns and paradigms 
    such as MVC (Model View Controller),
    Convention over Configuration
    and DRY (Don&#8217;t Repeat Yourself) code.
    In short,
    Rails makes web applications faster to develop and easier to maintain.
  </p>

